As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 173 people, 72 households, and 51 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|119.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 77 housing units at an average density of {{convert|53.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}. The racial makeup of the town was 83.82% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] and 16.18% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]]. By 2020, its population declined to 153.

